    {
      "id": "129f8e475b2067a8163acc9f0bab4598abcb25bf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 458,
        "name": "Olaf Faaland",
        "email": "faaland1@llnl.gov",
        "username": "ofaaland"
      },
      "date": "2018-04-03 17:15:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBrian wrote:\n> Thanks for the clarification.  We've got another round of\n> dnode_hold() performance improvements in the works which I\n> hope will make dnode_hold() fast enough.  I'll make sure\n> to add you to the PR when I open it.\n>\n> Alternately, I'd be OK with exploring the idea of adding a\n> version of `dmu_object_alloc_dnsize()` which returns the\n> dnode_t with the hold.  That way, Lustre won't need to\n> directly call any of the refcount functions.\n\nHave either of these proposals moved forward, so osd-zfs does not need to alter the refcount like this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "48a95e83260b653c482015d85d9491f7bcc4cac3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-31 10:56:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nBrian, the patch as it currently stands looks reasonably simple to me.  Does it make sense to land this patch as-is to resolve the problem with building on ZFS master, and then discuss further work to clean up this code in a separate patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5d5a4719b07e7dd5531e7edc5dbacf2599e579a6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 528,
        "name": "Brian Behlendorf",
        "email": "behlendorf1@llnl.gov",
        "username": "behlendo"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-31 16:04:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nAndreas, yes I'm in favor of landing the fix as-is to resolve the immediate build issue.  We can work on further improvements in a different patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
